eNCA's Pule Letshwiti-Jones is following this story. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police are on high alert in Diepsloot on Friday. Minister Bheki Cele says at least 16 new police vehicles have been deployed. Residents say police are failing to deal with high levels of crime in the area. Diepsloot has faced two days of protests and an attack in which a Zimbabwean man Elvis Nyati was murdered. He said, "you can go and see the 16 new police vans that we've sent to this station. It's 16 cars." "Another thing is that today the Police Commissioner that we have here says the police will be on the ground." "They will be on the ground until we come back to monitor the situation."